    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Setting <em>forever</em> aside, where do you think we would end up after an additional 10 partial sums? Would we cross the dotted red line? How many sums would you take before you decided that the <em>series</em> never crosses the line?</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">A cousin of this series is the Harmonic Series. We’ve seen <a href="https://towardsdatascience.com/two-concise-proofs-of-harmonic-series-divergence-8b69f1aa8e66" target="_self">elsewhere</a> that this series never quits. It continues to grow.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
