    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Each successive term of the Basel Problem is less than its corresponding Harmonic Series term. The partial sums will always be below those of the Harmonic Series. That’s little help, since Basel’s cousin has no ceiling.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
